  <prompt>
    Author Phase B integration tests against dev BFF: each of the 5 endpoints (happy path + 403 read-deny + cache behavior for the 3 cached endpoints). Critical: include the cross-entity privilege bypass test on `/fetch` per ADR-008 (privilege escalation via `&lt;link-entity&gt;` must return 403). Honors the `bff-extensions.md` test-update obligation.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in `WebApplicationFactory` integration test harness, mocked Dataverse `ServiceClient`, and ASP.NET Core auth test patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Integration test suite under `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Api/Dataverse/` covers happy path + 403 + cache (3 endpoints) + cross-entity privilege bypass (`/fetch`); `dotnet test` passes; CI runs them on PR.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-BFF-01..07 acceptance criteria and the `bff-extensions.md` test-update obligation. The cross-entity privilege bypass test is the most important security test ‚Äî it verifies the FetchXML privilege analyzer (task 013) actually catches `<link-entity>` escalation. Use `WebApplicationFactory` with a `ServiceClient` mock for happy paths and a restricted-user mock for 403 paths. Cache hit-rate tests use the in-memory IDistributedCache via the dev profile.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Api/Dataverse/SavedQueryEndpointsTests.cs</file>
      <file>tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Api/Dataverse/MetadataEndpointTests.cs</file>
