  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the test suite, when run via `dotnet test`, then all tests pass.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the cross-entity privilege bypass test (FetchXML with `&lt;link-entity name="restricted"&gt;`), when called by user without Read on `restricted`, then 403 ProblemDetails returned.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the cache-hit test for `/savedquery/{id}`, when called twice within 1 hour, then ServiceClient mock receives only 1 call (second call is cache hit).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given `/metadata/{entity}` for representative entity, when response measured, then &lt;50KB.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given CI workflow, when integration tests run, then they execute as part of PR checks (not skipped).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The cross-entity privilege bypass test (step 4) is THE most important test in this suite. If it fails, it indicates a security gap ‚Äî coordinate with reviewer before proceeding to task 017 (deploy). Per `bff-extensions.md` D-05/T-022 enforcement model: PR template + code review (NOT a CI script) catches missing test updates, so the obligation is owned by Claude + reviewer here.
  </notes>

  <execution>
